Xi analysis

While examining the effect of diagnosis on Xi methylation, the effects of cell type proportions and batches will be controlled for. As inflation of p-values was observed in a previous analysis, the model will now include principal components.

Thee PCs will first be correlated to diagnosis, to make sure that they do not remove wanted variance from the regression model. In the case of a significant (p<0.05) correlation, the relevant PCs will be removed.

The principal components that correlate with diagnosis (PC 1,2,5) will be left out of the analysis, and only PCs 3,4,6,7, and 8 will be added to the model. To determine the best model, five different models have been run, with increasing numbers of principal components.
